Discover the evidence-backed system that guarantees better academic results.

When I was 17, I had a dream to become a doctor.

I entered pre-med, fully aware of the fierce competition that awaited me. 

I locked myself in an intense routine, waking up at 7 AM for lectures and studying until midnight, every single day.

One day, a classmate casually mentioned studying until 2 AM. I felt compelled to outdo him and started studying 20 hours a day, every day, for nine gruelling months. 

I even resorted to rubbing dissolved breath mints on my eyelids to stay awake. Every second mattered…

The result? I got perfect grades and made it to medical school, but at the cost of my mental health.

In medical school, the volume of content doubled, and my previous method of studying 20 hours a day was unsustainable. 

I remembered walking out of a lecture after week 1 telling myself, “There is no way I can keep up anymore…”...

I knew I needed a better approach if I wanted to do well without repeating last year’s struggles.

Over the next few years, I dove into thousands of research papers on learning, constantly building on the techniques I’d picked up from medicine.

Eventually, I was confident enough to teach what I had refined to the students I tutored, and it worked!

This obsession led me back to university, where I completed a Master’s in Education scoring the highest grade in every paper and was awarded the Dean's award for the top graduating student in the program.

And I only studied a few hours a day for 6 weeks…

I discovered that many students, like myself, were stuck in a cycle of intense work, inconsistent results, and anxiety. 

The methods we were using were inefficient and unsustainable. 

Recognizing this, I left my medical career to teach these effective learning skills full-time. 

Today, I work with tens of thousands of people from over 150 countries, helping them learn more efficiently and achieve their academic goals without burning out.

The reality is that most studying does not lead to learning. By actually understanding how learning works, you can transform your approach and achieve extraordinary results with less effort. 

This program is designed to help you unlock your true potential and change your life, just like it did for me.

What I realised about becoming a top learner (after 13 years)...

To become a top learner, you need to understand 3 things...

  • First, you still need to work hard. There's no magic pill to become an ultra-learner overnight.

  • Second, becoming a top learner means changing your habits. If you're not willing to change, don't expect anything to change!

  • Third, making the change is worth it to achieve the goals you want to achieve.

Seems simple?

Here's the thing...

Most people do not make this change.

Most people stick with their same learning methods for years, endlessly playing catch up and losing opportunities.

In over a decade of coaching people to become top learners, the most important thing I've realised is that even if you teach someone "the best learning methods", it doesn't matter if they're still held back by something else.

So what holds students back?

Why do so few students actually succeed with their studies?

Outdated learning methods

Problem: If you spend hours studying without getting the results you want, the problem is how you study (effort isn't the issue!).

Procrastination

Problem: If you can't control procrastination, you can't control your life. You cannot achieve any goal reliably if you're a slave to procrastination.

Low focus and energy

Problem: You blocked out 4 hours to study. But you spend 2 hours distracted and 1 hour napping. Sound familiar? Me too.

Lack of control

Problem: Imagine trying to fix a car without knowing how an engine works... That's what trying to get better grades without knowing how learning works is like.

Burnout

Problem: Burnout = Effort without reward. Taking a break isn't always enough to overcome burnout at its root cause.

Balancing life

Problem: There's more to life than studying. But when studying is so stressful, it's hard to enjoy life outside of it!

How our program helps you save time and get better results.

It took me a decade of trial and error to figure out how to learn with true efficiency. I want you to learn that in less than 1/10th of the time.

  • Write high-efficiency notes that help you remember more in less time

What to expect as you work through the program...

These are our five steps for better grades.

Step 1: Theory

Understand how the brain likes to learn (based on the research).

Step 2: Tools

Learn tried-and-tested techniques based on the theory.

Step 3: Apply

Practise the techniques in your studies with our step-by-step instructions.

Step 4: Feedback

Improve faster by getting support, feedback and guidance on your work.

Step 5: Thrive

Save time every week with your growing learning efficiency!

The road to becoming a highly efficient learner

Click the tabs below to see a breakdown of what to expect in your journey.

Day 1: Uncover your learning habits

Start your journey with a detailed learning diagnostic assessment that assess you on five evidence-based dimensions of learning:

  1. Deep processing: Your ability to analyse concepts, create connections, and extract meaningful learning from information. Deep processing is what most people think of as "intelligence".

  2. Self-regulation: Your awareness of how you learn and your ability to make strategic changes to your methods. Self-regulation is what creates an adaptable learner.

  3. Retrieval: Your strategies for memory retrieval and developing mastery. Retrieval influences your ability to recall information quickly and solve complex problems.

  4. Self-management: Your time, task, stress, and focus management skills and habits. Self-management is the defining characteristic of consistently productive people.

  5. Mindset: Your beliefs and tendencies around learning from mistakes, experimentation, and navigating uncertainty. Mindset is the single most important attribute for rapid growth and improvement.

At the end, you'll get a personalised report with your specific learning strengths and weaknesses alongside practical recommendations for how you can immediately improve your most high-yield dimensions.

Week 1: High-yield improvements

Train your highest priority areas with a suite of rapid-fire learning and self-management techniques. Some of our students fix their biggest barriers in just this first stage.

During this week, you'll learn how to:

  1. Schedule and create focus zones

  2. Reduce procrastination (for good)

  3. Create task lists that actually work

  4. Use spaced interleaved retrieval to boost memory and knowledge mastery

  5. "Stack" marginal gains to unlock the secret to faster skill improvement and growth

Weeks 2 to 10: Rapid growth

Fill your learning toolkit and build a truly top learner's system. Expect heavy hitting techniques that help you nail the next exam (and every exam for the rest of your life).

In this stage, you'll learn to:

  1. Use evidence-based note-taking techniques that enhance memory and deepen understanding (that don't take all day)

  2. Process information during class and lectures to prevent overwhelm and retain more of what you hear

  3. Use flashcards like a top learner, including our flashcard "rule of 3" and "active flashcard management" system

  4. Prepare for exams with more confidence while minimising gaps and errors.

  5. Learn new skills 10 to 20x faster than normal with our famous modified Kolb's cycle (one of our foundational techniques for hacking growth).

Weeks 10 to 20: Become a genius

You've got a great learning system already.

You might have already achieve your goals and you don't even need to get any better! But if you're aiming for the very top, it's time to rewire the way your brain thinks and learns at a fundamental level.

Using our world's first cognitive retraining methodology, you'll learn:

  1. How to use advanced note-taking methods that drive higher-order learning

  2. High-pressure time management and habit creation systems to perform at your peak when everyone else struggles

  3. Advanced planning, motivation and stress management systems that can withstand the demands of the most difficult and competitive exams and careers.

Week 20+: Road to mastery

At the stage, you'll learn:

  1. How to hyper-personalise your learning system for any situation and challenge

  2. How to create advanced learning systems for complicated challenges and limited time

  3. How to combine and hybridise all the techniques you've learned so far to overcome unique challenges and reach the highest level of academic success

Note that the expected timeline for improvements depends on your level of practice and diligence. The expectations above are based on our recommended 2 to 3 hours of theory per week. Individual results may vary.

So, does it work for my subject/curriculum?

Our academic program is suitable for a very wide range of domains and circumstances. This is because the techniques are built on fundamental methods of human processing, rather than superficial, subject-specific tips or tricks.

For subjects:

It is most effective for subjects that are heavy, conceptual or detailed. For example:

  • sciences

  • medicine

  • maths

  • anatomy

  • philosophy

  • english

  • economics

  • law/politics

  • coding

It is least effective for highly procedural domains such as music performance, dance and (partially) languages.

For curriculums:

We have learners using our program successfully for the following curriculums:

  • MCAT

  • IGCSE/GCSE

  • A-levels

  • IB

  • USMLE

  • UPSC

  • JEE

  • NEET

  • SAT

There are also many learners studying for professional certifications like CA/CPA/CFA examinations, medical and surgical specialisation exams, and software certifications.

Who is this program not suitable for?

We do not recommend this program if...

  • You’re not ready to put in the time and effort...


    You will need to commit to at least 2 hours of theory and reflection per week (and practise what you learn in your normal daily studying). If you’re not able or ready to commit this time, you may not see results as quickly or easily.

  • You’re not willing to try something new and experiment with your learning...

    Unless you're already a hyper-efficient learner, you'll need to change your current methods and habits. This can be uncomfortable and challenging. If you do not feel ready or willing to experiment and persevere through discomfort, this program is not for you.

  • You’re not willing to make any mistakes...

    Learning something new always involves making mistakes. If you're not willing to make some mistakes and learn from them, you will struggle to improve. If this is you, we do not recommend the program for you.

  • You’re looking for a magic bullet or a "get-smart-quick" scheme...

    This program isn't a 30-second TikTok tip. There’s no secret shortcut to academic excellence. If you're looking for an overnight solution, this program is not for you.

I will teach you the best practices, but your success depends on your effort and commitment.

The one thing I can guarantee is that if you apply these strategies consistently and put in the effort, you’ll find it incomparably easier and simpler to achieve your academic goals, in less time.

If that sounds like something you’d like, then this program is for you.

If it’s not what you’re looking for, then thank you for considering us, and we wish you the very best of luck in your studies.

Frequently Asked Questions

Do I need to have any prior knowledge before taking the iCanStudy Academic Program?

No prior knowledge is required. Our program is designed to help students of all levels, from high school to graduate students and lifelong learners. Whether you’re struggling with basic study habits or looking to refine advanced techniques, we have you covered.

How can I be sure this program will be effective for me?

We understand the scepticism, which is why our program is backed by years of research and practical application. We’ve helped thousands of students improve their study habits and achieve their academic goals. Plus, we offer a 30-Day Money Back Guarantee if you complete the course and don’t see the results you expected.

Will this program address my specific needs?

Our program is tailored to fit a wide range of learning styles and academic levels. We offer personalised support and strategies to ensure that you get the most out of the program, regardless of your unique situation.

How much does the program cost, and is it worth the investment?

While the cost of the program might seem high, think of it as an investment in your academic future. The skills and techniques you learn will save you time, reduce stress, and help you achieve better results.

What if I’m already using another study method or program?

Our techniques are designed to complement and enhance any existing study methods you might be using. Many of our students have successfully integrated our strategies with other programs to achieve even better results.

What makes the iCanStudy Academic Program different from other study programs?

Our program is based on scientifically-proven techniques and years of research. We focus on higher-order thinking skills, personalised learning plans, and efficient study methods that go beyond traditional rote memorization.

What kind of support will I receive during the program?

You’ll have access to a community of learners and support from experienced coaches. We provide personalised guidance - you’ll have access to an entire team of seasoned experts who are here to help you overcome any challenges you might encounter.

How do I know if this program is the right fit for me?

If you’re serious about improving your study habits and achieving academic excellence, this program is for you. We provide the tools and support needed to help you succeed, but you must be willing to put in the effort and apply what you learn.

I still have questions, what's the best way to get in touch?

We're here to help! The best way to reach out is by clicking the little speech bubble icon found down the bottom right hand corner of the page, this will connect you with our team who will be more than happy to assist.
